	<div class="portlet-body">



	
		
			
			
				
					



























































































































	

				

				
					
					
						


	
	
		

































































	
	

		

		
			
			

				

				
					

						

						
						
						
					    
						
						<div class="journal-content-article asd">
							<section class="kelafi-article">

				<h1>Temporary compensation due to an epidemic outbreak for basic social assistance clients</h1>

<p>The purpose of the temporary compensation is to support the most vulnerable persons and families who have incurred extra costs as a result of the restrictions imposed due to the coronavirus epidemic.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The compensation will be paid for four months&nbsp;(September to December 2020). The temporary compensation can be granted to persons who have received basic social assistance for part of the time or for the whole time that the restrictions due to the coronavirus epidemic have been in force, 1 March - 31 July 2020. A further requirement is that the person has received basic social assistance in the month preceding payment of the compensation. This means for instance that compensation can be paid for September if the client has received basic social assistance in August.</p>

<h2><span style="color: rgb(0, 52, 127); font-family: MetaWeb, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 36px;">You do not need to apply for the compensation</span></h2>

<p>Kela grants compensation due to an epidemic outbreak automatically to all clients who are entitled to it. It is thus not necessary to apply for the compensation separately.</p>

<p>However, it has emerged that there may some cases where a client may be entitled to temporary compensation due to the coronavirus epidemic, but Kela is not able to automatically retrieve data on that client.</p>

<p>Please contact Kela, if you did not receive temporary compensation on 16 October and you meet the following requirements:</p>

<ul>
	<li>you have not yourself applied for basic social assistance during 2020</li>
	<li>you have been a member of a family that received basic social assistance during the period from 1 March to 31 July 2020</li>
	<li>you have, after July 2020, moved to live with another family and this family receives basic social assistance.</li>
</ul>

<p>It may, for example, be a situation where there has been a change in marital status or family composition, or a child has become independent and moved from home.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Also contact Kela if you meet the following two requirements:</p>

<ul>
	<li>you have received basic social assistance for part of the time or for the whole time that the restrictions due to the coronavirus epidemic have been in force, 1 March - 31 July 2020</li>
	<li>you have been granted social assistance for the period 1 August 2020–30 November 2020 and</li>
	<li>after you received that decision, you received income which caused the decision to be reviewed and reversed.</li>
</ul>

<p>Such income could for example be a housing allowance granted with retroactive effect. If you meet the above requirements, you may have a right to temporary compensation due to an epidemic outbreak even if you were denied social assistance following a review.</p>

<h2>Amount and payment dates</h2>

<p>The amount of the compensation due to an epidemic outbreak is €75 per month and per person. Half the regular amount, or EUR 37.50 per month, is paid for a child who lives alternately in two different homes.&nbsp;The benefit is not subject to tax. It does not affect the social assistance or any other benefits.</p>

<p>The payment dates are:</p>

<ul>
	<li>compensation for September, 16 October 2020</li>
	<li>compensation for October, 16 October 2020</li>
	<li>compensation for November, 16 November 2020</li>
	<li>compensation for December, 16 December 2020</li>
</ul>

<p>In Åland, the payment dates will be confirmed later, as the government of Åland will rewiev the law separately.</p>

<p>You can check the temporary compensation granted to you by <a href="https://www.kela.fi/web/en/e-services">signing in to our e-services</a>. The notice of decision concerning the temporary compensation will appear on the e-services portal a few days before the date of payment. It will be listed under basic social assistance. A written notice of decision will be mailed to your home address.</p>

<h2>If you are dissatisfied with your decision</h2>

<p>If you think that the decision you received on temporary compensation due to an epidemic outbreak is wrong, you can appeal to have it changed.</p>

<p>You can file an appeal through our e-services or by letter. The appeal must be submitted to Kela within 37 days of the date of mailing of the decision you are appealing. The date of mailing is shown on the decision. If you wish, you can use a specific <a href="https://www.kela.fi/documents/10192/3861304/VAL1e.pdf">form for appeals</a> when writing your appeal.<br />
If you do not wish to use the form, be sure to tell the following</p>

<ul>
	<li>your name, personal identity code, phone number and address at which you wish to receive letters and decision notices concerning the appeal</li>
	<li>the decision you are appealing</li>
	<li>how you want the decision to be changed</li>
	<li>why you want the decision to be changed.</li>
</ul>

<p>The decision will be re-examined by Kela and, if found to be wrong, amended. The amended decision will be mailed to you.</p>

<p>If Kela considers that it cannot amend the decision in the way you want, it will forward your appeal to the Social Security Appeal Board. You have a further right of appeal to the Insurance Court, which is the highest court of appeal. Both will provide you with a written decision on your appeal.</p>

<p>Please note that the appeal procedure is different from that used in cases involving basic social assistance. <a href="https://www.kela.fi/web/en/from-an-application-to-a-decision_how-to-appeal-a-decision">Read more on how to appeal a decision</a>.</p>
	
				
			
			
									
	
